						               													<description>This game is just like many other werewolf games.&amp;#10;However, this game is suitable for all players, even for new players.&amp;#10;The difference is that each cards at the bottom there is either a + or a - which tells you the difficulty for each team. +sign for villagers team, and a -sign for the werewolf team.&amp;#10;Furthermore this game has 19 different characters. Below are the characters that appear in the game with their difficulty sign:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Villager: +1 (3 different art 5 each type in box)&amp;#10;Werewolf: -6 (3 different art 2 each type in box)&amp;#10;Prophet: +7 &amp;#10;Prophet's Apprentice: +4&amp;#10;Medium: +2&amp;#10;Body Guard +3&amp;#10;Twins: +2 (2 cards in box)&amp;#10;Werewolf Possessed Human: -1&amp;#10;Tough Guy: +3&amp;#10;Crazy Person: -3&amp;#10;Fox Demon: +-0&amp;#10;Hunter: +4&amp;#10;Cursed: -3&amp;#10;King: +2&amp;#10;Dictator: +3&amp;#10;Prophet's Mother: +5&amp;#10;Trap Master: +4&amp;#10;Teen Werewolf: -4&amp;#10;Copycat: -1&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So if you would like to make an easy game just make either side + or - or a normal game which would be +-0.&amp;#10;(Note all the rest have only 1 cards each in the box)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are also 10 summary cards to let players view the effects and powers of each characters for easy playing.&amp;#10;Japanese required to translate the effects, but once you memorize it is really fun to play!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
